The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Learner crushes woman
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Learner crushes woman
          OUR BUREAU                               
	A woman in her early 40s was crushed under the wheels of an Ambassador after its driver lost control and mounted a pavement in Chetla on Monday.        
	The driver, a young woman, sped away after hitting Arati Mondal on 2H Alipur Avenue around 3.40pm.        
	Mondal died on way to SSKM Hospital.        
	Later in the evening, police spotted the vehicle in Sarsuna, Behala. The fatal squad of the traffic police has started a probe into the incident.        
	Witnesses gave us the vehicles registration number and we traced the car owner. The woman was learning to drive and lost control, the police said.        
	More mishaps: Three persons were killed and nine injured in three accidents on the northern fringes of the city on Monday.        
	Around 6.45am, the dumper of a construction company hit Swapan Den, 17, at Dasadrone in Rajarhat. Swapan was cycling towards New Town Road when he was hit from behind, said Mrityunjay Dhole, the owner of the tea-stall where Swapan worked.        
	Swapan was taken to a nursing home, where he was declared dead. The dumper was seized and the driver arrested.        
	An hour later, a speeding truck hit two youths  Samir Mondal and Mithun Mondal  on a motorcycle in the Nayabandh area of Rajarhat.        
	Samir was declared dead when he was taken to a nursing home. Mithuns condition was critical.        
	Around 7pm, a speeding Tata Sumo mounted a pavement in Barasat and hit an eight-year-old girl and eight others. The unidentified girl died on the spot, police said.                                                                                                                                                                         
